	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				*SPOILER*<BR>
<BR>
The Trueshot Bow quest is long and difficult, mostly because of the high fletching skill you need to finish the job.  Start with the bag you get off the guild master.  Head to Freeport.  There are two Jyle Windshots...one is in Seafarer's Roost right by the docks.  He wants a Faydark Champion's Tunic and 2gp.  Being that I didn't have the tunic I almost gave up the quest there.  Then I found the other Jyle at an inn in West Freeport not far from the gate.  That one wanted a small lantern (easily obtainable) in exchange he gives you the Treant Wood Shards, some faction, and some xp (unnoticable at my level).   I'd suggest getting several because the boat ride is a long time spent twidling your thumbs (or trading languages).<BR>
<BR>
On the boat ride back from Freeport stop off at Sisterhood Island (it's the only stop in that direction), run to the nearest hut, turn left, and buy a bunch of kiola nuts from the merchant.  You need two for every dwarven wire you want to get.  Unfortunately, they don't stack, so have plenty of backpacks.  If you're quick, you can hop back on the boat before it leaves, otherwise you'll have a long wait ahead of you for the next boat.<BR>
<BR>
Back ashore in Butcherblock, zone into Kaladim, turn left past the entrance and the second building on your right (I think) is Irontoe's bar.  Give him 1 kiloa nut and 1 flask of water and he'll give you a Trumpy Tonic.  You need 2 tonics for every dwarven wire, so stock up. These do stack.<BR>
<BR>
Next head over to Everhot's Forge on the other side of Kaladim (you zone to get to it--look at the map in your book).  Sometimes he's not there (wandering around the mines), but he usually returns soon.  Give him 2 trumpy tonics (one each in separate slots!) and he'll give you a spool of dwarven wire, xp, and some faction.  The wire spools also stack, but they will not go into the bank, so I'd save getting the wire until you're already a master fletcher (or you have one lined up to do the job for you).<BR>
<BR>
Next stop is Steamfont.  Kill the rogue clockworks (not the regular ones).  The rogue clockwork faction seems busted...at least they still don't attack me on sight and I've killed a hundred.  [I can't get into Ak'anon but that's because a merchant there has a thing against my diety.]  These clockworks give on rare occasion micro servos (about a 1 in 10 shot I think..maybe worse).  You might do better to auction for them instead if you're the impatient type; of course if you're the impatient type this quest isn't for you.  Word of warning...a Minotaur Hero sometimes appears in the area.  He will kill you if he sees you.  Run to the windmills and the guard there will generally finish him off.  (Be nice, and shout out a warning while you're running for your life.)  He still cons red to me, but I will exact my revenge some day.<BR>
<BR>
The spiderling silk is the easiest component to get, you can be nice and buy it off the newbies, or spend more at the merchants, or just kill the spiderlings yourself.  I presume this is different from spider silk, so watch for the slight difference in terms (kind of like how 'an orc warrior' is different from 'a orc warrior').<BR>
<BR>
Put ONE of each component into the bag and click combine and give the bag to Trueshot.  He'll give you a Treant Bow Staff, xp, and faction.  The staff is a lore item, so you can only have one (if you repeat and you already have one you do not get another and you lose the combined bag).  The staff can go into the bank, though I doubt two will.<BR>
<BR>
Now with all this done, hopefully you have a nice, high fletching skill because this bow is difficult to make.  The lowest skill I've heard of with anyone successful at making the bow is 106.  Mine is 70, and I'm going bankrupt trying to raise it.  I've heard someone with a 161 skill was successful 2 out of 7 tries.  This is why you got extra components, right?<BR>
<BR>
To make the bow: the fletching kit can be bought at the Fletcher's shop or off the merchant who sells arrow components (I forget which...they're on the same platform in Kelethin).  The planing tool can be bought off the merchant who sells bow making items (who is on the same platform as the Trueshot Bow shop--too bad they don't sell their namesake).  The micro servo and dwarven wire you already know how to get.  Put the treant wood bow staff, micro servo, dwarven wire, and planing tool into the fletching kit (one of each) and click combine.  With luck you have a Trueshot Bow.  Otherwise you have spare components (right?), so go back for another bag from Trueshot, fill it, and try again.<BR>
<BR>
This quest is quite time-consuming and the resulting item is marketable only to rangers, so it is rare to see a Trueshot Bow sold.  I've heard one auctioned at 100pp...don't know if it sold.  Seems to me someone is taking a loss since it's going to cost me close to that just to get my Fletching skill high enough!  On the plus side, making 150 range high damage arrows will be trivial.  
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
